 For installing using the default options just do:

    make install

 This will compile the daemon, put the executable into /usr/sbin,
 create the folder /var/lib/amprd and put an example config file
 named amprd.conf.example into /etc

 Edit the config file to your needs (all parameters are described there)
 and rename it to amprd.conf

 If you like a custom install, edit the path of the files in "commons.h",
 issue a 'make clean' and 'make' and setup the system to your liking.


 Have fun with amateur radio!

                                      Marius, YO2LOJ
